      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a weird loud humming sound but the fan isnt actually spinning. its just sitting there vibrating and humming. what could be causing that and is it safe for me to go look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That humming sound without spinning is likely caused by a capacitor failure, a seized motor, or a blocked condenser fan, which can prevent the fan from starting despite receiving power. It is generally not safe to go look at it immediately because the unit is under high voltage and could still be live even after a power outage; additionally, the vibrating components risk further damage or injury if you try to touch them. You should turn off the power to the unit at the breaker and call a licensed HVAC technician to diagnose and repair the issue professionally.",
